Glob patterns + |variant syntax combined

Two orthogonal features:
1. Globs: ~event transform.* matches family of events
2. Variants: ~proc event|gpu provides target-specific impl

Combined: ~proc transform.*|gpu = GPU impl for ALL transforms

Parser must accept:
- ~event module:name.* { ... }         (glob declaration)
- ~proc module:name.*|variant { ... }  (glob + variant)

Variant selection happens at:
- Compile time (build config: --target=gpu)
- Or runtime dispatch (if multiple variants compiled in)

Use cases:
- GPU/CPU/WASM variants for image processing family
- Debug/release variants for logging family
- Platform-specific variants (linux/windows/macos)
